Incredible images show handcuffed members from the notorious Barrio 18 gang being moved from Izalco jail to San Francisco Gotera in an effort to curb gang violence . 
  In all 1,177 Barrio members will mix with rivals from the hyper-violent Mara Salvatrucha gang, or MS-13 . 
  The move is in a bid to stop the gangs running operations from behind bars . 
  Violence in El Salvador has increased after a 2012 truce between the two gangs . 
 